-When soloing your prime consideration should always be your HPs<br>
-Keep turg/torg up when you will be slowing often to avoid recast delay problems.<br>
-On bigger pulls, always slow the adds before the main target, unless your enc has 1000/2500 unbuffed or something<br>
-Always keep a Journeyman's Walking Stick handy for yourself or a tank to use at beginning of fights when no enc is present<br>
-Cast heals (SH/Blast) on any close tank CH, you can always duck out if you realize it's unnecessary<br>
-Keep a DA Idol on some sort of easily accessible hotkey at all times, they're cheap and can get you out of a lot of sticky situations<br>
-Get a Shovel of Ponz, reclaim energy, castable from inventory. Great for when you need to zone, or for using your pet as a spare mana battery.<br>
<br>
Buffing<br>
Make a hotkey for OOC, Group, and Guild, saying something along these lines: &quot;Send tells for buffs, be specific, and concise or you ain't getting shit.&quot; Unless you've got nothing better to do, don't bother with dex buffs (or use JBG), and never buff rangers. Always keep the people you dislike or who are in the lowest position of power last on the buff list.<br>
<br>
Gear<br>
Go with an AC set and a resists set. Try to get a fungi tunic and/or staff (unless you're torpor enabled), in terms of cannibalize tunic+staff is like Flowing Thought XX. I forget where the quest spoiler is but there are some 25 pr/dr gloves, easy quest.<br>
<br>
As far as sites go, the big one is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/forumdisplay.php?s=6fee9cb996817648e098744bc46de760&amp;forumid=479">The Shaman's Crucible</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, over 100k posts.<br>
<br>
